<h2>Brew Method: Aeropress</h2>
<div class=brew-description>
  <div class=brewimage>
      <%= image_tag "thumbs/coffee-experiments-aeropress.png", :style => "width: 80px" %>
  </div>
  <p>
    An immersion, filtered, and high extraction method from pressure to make a strong espresso like brew. This method can be performed in a variety of ways.  Can be prepared using the inverted or non-inverted method. Key identifiers are smooth, full flavor, and refined.
  </p>
</div>


<h3 class=brew-title>Instructions: Inverted Method</h3>
<div>

  <div class=instructions>
      <div style="float: left">
        <%= image_tag "thumbs/coffee-experiments-instructions-aeropress1.png",:width => "100px", :style=>"margin-left: 50px; margin-right: 30px"%>
    </div>

      <p class=instructionsleft>1. Assemble the plunger into the main vessel so the rubber stopper is aligned with the bottom of the “4”.</p>
  </div>

  <div class=instructions>
      <div style="float: right">
        <%= image_tag "thumbs/coffee-experiments-instructions-aeropress2.png",:width => "100px", :style=>"margin-left: 35px; margin-right: 50px"%>
    </div>

      <p class=instructionsright>2. Pour pre-heated water into the aeropress to rinse and warm the brew vessel. Discard water into the mug to warm the drinking vessel as well.</p>
  </div>

  <div class=instructions>
      <div style="float: left">
        <%= image_tag "thumbs/coffee-experiments-instructions-aeropress3.png",:width => "100px", :style=>"margin-left: 50px; margin-right: 30px"%>
    </div>

      <p class=instructionsleft>3. Grind 2 scoops of beans in a burr grinder. Using the funnel, put them in the aeropress. Give a gentle shake to even the bed of grounds.</p>
  </div>

  <div class=instructions>
      <div style="float: right">
        <%= image_tag "thumbs/coffee-experiments-instructions-aeropress4.png",:width => "100px", :style=>"margin-left: 35px; margin-right: 50px"%>
    </div>

      <p class=instructionsright>4. Pour enough water into the vessel to cover the bed of grounds. Make sure there are no air pockets and all beans are saturated. Start the timer and bloom for 30sec.</p>
  </div>

  <div class=instructions>
    <div style="float: left">
        <%= image_tag "thumbs/coffee-experiments-instructions-aeropress5.png",:width => "100px", :style=>"margin-left: 50px; margin-right: 30px"%>
    </div>

      <p class=instructionsleft>5. Pour the remaining water up to the top of the “1” mark.</p>
  </div>

  <div class=instructions>
    <div style="float: right">
        <%= image_tag "thumbs/coffee-experiments-instructions-aeropress6.png",:width => "100px", :style=>"margin-left: 35px; margin-right: 50px"%>
    </div>

      <p class=instructionsright>6. At 1 minute on the timer, place the filter in the filter cap and attach firmly on the top of the press. (Remember to remove the pre-heat water from step 2 <i>before</i> adding coffee to the mug!)</p>
  </div>

  <div class=instructions>
    <div style="float: left">
        <%= image_tag "thumbs/coffee-experiments-instructions-aeropress7.png",:width => "100px", :style=>"margin-left: 50px; margin-right: 30px"%>
    </div>

      <p class=instructionsleft>7. Carefully invert the whole apparatus onto the drinking vessel, and over 15-20sec press down on the plunger to push the water through the beans into the drinking vessel. <i> Note: the funnel can be used inbetween the aeropress and mug if the mug mouth is too narrow for the aeropress. </i></p>
  </div>

  <div class=instructions>
      <div style="float: right">
        <%= image_tag "thumbs/coffee-experiments-instructions-aeropress8.png",:width => "100px", :style=>"margin-left: 35px; margin-right: 50px"%>
    </div>

      <p class=instructionsright>8. Enjoy this very strong brew, or add enough hot water to fill the drinking vessel (total liquid will be about 300ml).</p>
  </div>

</div>

